games.description:
Domino Online Multiplayer: Challenge Your Mind in Exciting Domino Duels!

Are you ready for a thrilling battle of wits and strategy? Domino Online Multiplayer brings the classic game of dominoes to your screen with exciting multiplayer options and engaging features. Play for free and without registration — dive into the world of dominoes and test your skills against various opponents!

Why choose Domino Online Multiplayer?

Multiple game modes:
- play against a computer with 9 difficulty levels (from Beginner to World Champion);
- engage in online duels with real players in real-time;
- send a link and play with a friend, even if you’re miles apart;
- enjoy a convenient «one-screen» mode for fun battles at home.

Flexible settings and features:
- choose from different time controls: Bullet, Blitz, Rapid, or Classic;
- use the move undo option to correct mistakes;
- benefit from hints that suggest the best move to help you learn on the fly;
- track your progress with a rating and detailed statistics;
- customize the look of the tiles and the playing field to suit your taste;
- review the move history to analyze your games and improve your strategy;
- exchange stickers and chat with your opponents to make the game more enjoyable.

Additional thrill:
Make bets and win gold from your opponents — add an extra layer of excitement to your matches!
Domino Online Multiplayer offers a challenging and entertaining experience for players of all levels. Join now and turn every game into an exciting challenge where every move brings you closer to victory!

games.howToPlayText:
Getting Started

Choose your game mode:
- play against the computer;
- engage in online duels with real players;
- play with a friend by sharing a link;
- enjoy a «one-screen» mode for playing with someone nearby.

Select your game settings:
- choose a time control mode (Bullet, Blitz, Rapid, or Classic);
- enable hints if you need help with your moves.

Game Rules and Gameplay

Setup:
- each player is dealt 7 domino tiles at the start of the game;
- the player with the lowest double (except for the blank tile) starts the game.

Making Moves:
- players take turns extending the domino chain on the table, matching the numbers on adjacent tiles;
- if a player doesn’t have a tile that matches the open ends of the chain, they must draw tiles from the bazaar (remaining tiles) until they find a matching one.

Winning a Round:
- the first player to play all their tiles wins the round;
- the losing player counts their penalty points, which are equal to the sum of the pips (dots) on their remaining tiles;
- special tiles: the 0-0 tile is worth 25 points, and the 6-6 tile is worth 50 points.

Ending a Round:
- if no player can make a move and the bazaar is empty, the round ends;
- the player with the fewest pips on their remaining tiles wins the round.

Scoring and Ending the Game:
- after each round, the next hand begins;
- the game continues until one player reaches 100 penalty points, at which point they are considered the loser of the entire game.

Enjoy the strategic challenge of Domino Online Multiplayer and see if you have what it takes to outwit your opponents!
